# {{.Name}}

An [MGO](https://github.com/mausamrijall/mgo) application — router: **{{.Router}}**, database: **{{.DB}}**.

## Run

```sh
mgo dev        # run with hot reload
go run .       # or plain go
go test ./...  # tests were generated too — keep them green
```

## Make things

```sh
mgo make handler posts    # new handler + test
mgo make provider cache   # new lifecycle provider
mgo swap router stdmux    # switch stack axes; your edits are never overwritten
```

## How this app is put together

- `main.go` — config, store, router, app lifecycle. Plain Go, ~30 lines.
- `router.go` — routes in {{.Router}}'s native API. MGO never wraps your router.
- `handlers.go` — plain `net/http` handlers; `web.JSON`/`web.Bind` are optional helpers.
{{if .HasDB}}- `store.go` — your data-access root; queries are native {{.DB}} code.
{{end}}- `mgo.json` — the stack manifest `mgo` uses for `swap`/`add`. Generated files are hash-tracked: once you edit one, `mgo` treats it as yours.

Delete MGO any time: what remains is ordinary Go.
